# Node.js CLI Task Tracker

This is a simple command-line interface (CLI) task tracker built with Node.js. It allows you to add, list, and complete tasks directly from your terminal.

## Features

- Add new tasks
- List all tasks
- Mark tasks as complete
- Delete tasks

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/nodejs-CLI-task-tracker.git
    ```
2. Navigate to the project directory:
    ```sh
    cd nodejs-CLI-task-tracker
    ```
3. Install the dependencies:
    ```sh
    npm install
    ```

## Usage

To use the task tracker, run the following commands:

- Add a new task:
    ```sh
    node index.js add "Your new task"
    ```

- List all tasks:
    ```sh
    node index.js list
    ```

- Mark a task as complete:
    ```sh
    node index.js complete <task_id>
    ```

- Delete a task:
    ```sh
    node index.js delete <task_id>
    ```

